		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You brandish your weapons or begin casting a spell, only to disappear in a burst of shadows or magical energy. You strike, then immediately teleport to your original position again.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You teleport up to 30 ft. to an unoccupied space on the ground, use your normal &amp;reference[attack] action from that position (with multiple attacks if applicable), then you teleport to your original position.</p></li><li><p>Your first attack on this turn has advantage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>At your GM's discretion, you might be able to use an action other than attacking if it's quick and doesn't require you to move from the position you teleport to.</em></p>",
